   BKN-KNICKS-MAGIC (New York) _ Orlando at Knicks, 1 p.m. By
Selena Roberts.
</P>
<P>
   RAC-REMSEN (New York) _ The Remsen and the Cigar Mile at
Aqueduct. By Joseph Durso.
</P>
<P>
   TEN-ATP (Berlin, Germany) _ ATP World Championships semifinals.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FEATURES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBC-HOKIES (Blacksburg) _ Its wait-and-see time for the
undefeated Virginia Tech Hokies, who concluded their regular season
Friday with a 35-14 rout of Boston College. By Joe Drape.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-GIANTS (East Rutherford, N.J.) _ As Kerry Collins prepares
to make his first start at Giants Stadium on Sunday, the question
is, will the Giants' offense be any better with him than it has
been with Kent Graham? By Bill Pennington.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-JETS (Indianapolis) _ The Jets face a balancing act in
Sunday's game at Indianapolis: They would like to start opening up
the offense with Ray Lucas gaining more experience and confidence
at quarterback. But this weekend they have to concentrate on
keeping the ball away from Peyton Manning, which puts the focus on
Curtis Martin and the Jets' running game. By Gerald Eskenazi.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ NFL notes and news; leading with an
item on the surprising competitiveness of the Chicago Bears. By
Mike Freeman.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ NBA notes and news: Lede item on the
animosity between Scottie Pippin and Charles Barkley. By Mike Wise.
</P>
<P>
   For information and repeats call the News Service at
1-888-603-1036. And be sure to look for other sports stories from
our partners: The Boston Globe, Cox News Service, Hearst News
Service, The Arizona Republic, Kansas City Star, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Los Angeles Daily News, San Francisco Chronicle and
Seattle Post-Intelligencer.
</P>
<P>
