<P>
   NIRELAND-UNIONISTS (Belfast, Northern Ireland) _ Opening the way
for the immediate startup of a new power-sharing administration in
Northern Ireland, the Ulster Unionist Party voted Saturday to
approve having its leaders enter a new government with their
ancient rivals from Sinn Fein, the political ally of the Irish
Republican Army. The yes vote sets off a series of steps by the
British and Irish governments, beginning on Monday, to transfer
power from the British Parliament in London to the new Northern
Ireland Assembly in the Stormont parliament building in Belfast by
Thursday. By Warren Hoge.
</P>
