   CROATIA-SUCCESSION (Zagreb, Croatia) _ The imminent death of
Croatia's founder and president, Franjo Tudjman, no matter who
succeeds him, will take much of the personal animosity and heat out
of the country's strained relationships with Washington and the
European Union, turning at least a part of the Balkans more firmly
westward, senior Croatian officials and Western diplomats say. By
Stephen Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   BRADLEY-FOREIGN (Washington) _ In his first major campaign event
on foreign policy, former Sen. Bill Bradley will use a meeting with
students on Monday to cast himself as a committed internationalist
who believes that America's vital interests abroad can best be
advanced through the free flow of goods, capital and ideas across
national boundaries, his aides said. By James Dao.
</P>
