</P>
<P>
   A few weeks ago, I had lunch with an English friend. It was a
typical lunch in an inexpensive cafe. We discussed our husbands,
our jobs and our hair, as one does, and then split the check and
went happily on our ways.
</P>
<P>
   When the mail came the next day, I was shocked to discover that
she had sent me a note.
</P>
<P>
   In fact, it was a note thanking me for lunch. What's more, my
friend had apparently gone out and bought an expensive card with a
picture that would mean something specifically to me. She had
mailed it off that very afternoon, at a time of day when all I had
