<P>
   SPORTS
</P>
<P>
   GLF-BECK _ He has lived in golf's version of hell for the past
two years. Chip Beck, a former Georgia golfer, isn't sure why his
golf game left him. Could have been personal problems that led to
the negative swing thoughts; could have been the very nature of the
game _ here one minute, gone the next. As the sport headed into its
final month, there was light. Beck, once one of the best golfers on
Tour, was playing better. And although he's a longshot to make
enough money to retain his Tour card, he thinks good things will
come. (Sheeley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25. MOVED
</P>
