LEND-HOUSING _ Phoenix has become a bright spot in getting
mortgages to minorities. The number of home loans to Hispanics and
African-Americans grew at a faster rate than mortgages to Anglos
during the past four years, unlike many other metropolitan areas.
Mortgages to African-Americans jumped nearly 92 percent from 1995
to 1998 in Phoenix. Conventional home loans for Hispanics rose by
74 percent, while lending to Anglos increased 68 percent. Story
will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
