   AHWATUKEE _ Ahwatukee Foothills fancied itself a suburban heaven
for the upwardly mobile _ the place to move for good schools, low
crime and mountain views. The name ``Ahwatukee'' itself, a Crow
Indian word for ``House of Your Dreams,'' reflected what thousands
hoped to find in Phoenix's promised land south of South Mountain.
But now, many residents in this community of 98,000 wonder whether
it's becoming a paradise lost. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
